column1: A SHARED SEEDBOX -  means more then you are using the Gbit/Cpu/Ram.
COMPANY - The vendors of the seedbox, and the link to their homepage
BOX NAME - Name of the box, so you can easly find it on the vendors homepage.
CPU - If you want to use the seedbox/stream with friends and family, is it important to chose a good CPU
TB - All listed seedboxes are SATA/HDD. See the tab SSD Seedboxes, if you want something quicker and more exspensive
GBIT SHARED - How good is your seedbox internet connection. The higher the number, the faster is both upload and download.
RAM - This detemind how fast your Seedbox is to example unpack a movie
TRAFFIC LIMIT - Unlimited means you can download and upload without restrictions.
LOCATION - Where the Seedbox is located. This is important, since the connection between you and the seedbox is also contolled by distance.
OPEN TRACKER - Do the seedbox allow puplic torrents, or only private trackers?
ROOT - If you got root acsees, can you install any software you wish. Beware if you are new, you need to learn alot, and install everything yourself.
PLEX - All listed Seedboxes are plex supported. Plex is media steaming software that works on almost all platforms.
PM me, if you find a seedbox missing on the list.
I hope to keep the list updated. Any hints on changes or updates, is more than welcome.
Before buying a seedbox "even if on this list", then make sure to check reddit, google, etc. for negative/positive comments.
The deference between 10 and 20 Gbit shared is laughable, almost what you would call a media stunt, since they usually have more people using the 20 gbit connection.
I would not recommend a seedbox with root, if this is your first time playing around with seedboxes, and just want  something that works the first time.
I have the best exprience with ping/upload speed with seedboxes located in Netherlands and Finland as close second.
All vendors got different payment options, but I would always recommend using paypal or crypto currency if possible.
This is only meant as reference, and what I look for in a seedbox. You might look for something else entirely

I'm running two seedboxes. 1st one is a SATA seedbox, that handle download/upload from private trackers, and got room for all my media. 2nd one, is a SSD, that sync up to the other, and have a better CPU/RAM for transcoding Plex faster.
1st SATA Seedbox: SDATA L from Seedhost.eu.
I'm NOT sharing my plex servers with friends or family, and if you want to do that, would I recommend somehting more powerful then my setup to handle transcoding and the traffic.
